author: National Geographic
description:
Dinner is served! This beaver kit is enjoying an evening meal of bark and cambium from a willow stick. And while this little one nibbles, its species shapes landscapes, proving that even the smallest engineers can be climate heroes. Wildfire mitigation and recovery are excellent examples of this, as the areas occupied by beavers show more resilience to the dangers. 

Learn more about how these semiaquatic rodents can help protect against the effects of climate change: https://on.natgeo.com/4pNDRoD
